U.S.-based Gospel Music Minister Joycelyn Chinwe believes that a joyful life melody is inspired by the teachings of Jesus Christ. The  Imo State, who has an enviable academic resume that saw her attending the Community College of Baltimore County (CCBC), University of Maryland, Baltimore County (UMBC), Coppin State University, and Walden University, says she is called to be an evangelical-inspirational singer to share the joy of Jesus Christ. 		 			Tems: I don’t force my songs		 		 		 			Top five Nollywood movies on Netflix in 2022		 		 		 			Don Jazzy signs young man who sang Wizkid, Davido’s…		 		 Chinwe’s central theme for music is ‘Jesus as the melody to a joyful life.’ According to Chinwe, the revelational message behind her ministry is that anyone who desires joyful life should seek Jesus as the melody behind such life. Since 2019, she yielded to the calling to serve God in music ministry, leading to the production of her first song in 2020; ‘God of Universe.’ She has four singles and an album of eight songs, ‘Joy Manifest’ released in March 2022. Some of her songs include More of Jesus, Jehovah the King, Joy Overflow, Greatest Love, Born to Rule, Onyeoma, and Calvary, among others.